This skill does NOT hand-maintain the ai-memory routing block.

Its canonical text is owned by the ai-memory binary (the `SNIPPET_BODY`
constant in `ai-memory-core`'s `routing_snippet.rs`). Keeping a copy here
would drift from the binary, so there isn't one.

Obtain the current block from the source and write it between the
`<!-- ai-memory:start -->` / `<!-- ai-memory:end -->` markers:

- Agent: call `memory_install_self_routing` (returns the block to Write/Edit).
- CLI:   `ai-memory install-instructions` (writes CLAUDE.md; `--target AGENTS.md`).

Both are idempotent (they replace whatever is between the markers). The
canonical block is generic — no workspace/project/server names, no page paths —
so it is safe to commit, including in a public repo.
